"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code sets the 'norm_hist' parameter to False, which means the histogram will show counts instead of density. However, the seaborn documentation states that if a KDE or fitted density is plotted, the histogram height should show a density rather than a count. Since the default behavior of 'distplot' is to include a KDE, setting 'norm_hist' to False is incorrect.\",\n  \"patch\": \"5c5\\n< sns.distplot(data.tip, norm_hist=False)\\n---\\n> sns.distplot(data.tip, norm_hist=True)\"\n}"